<paragraph id="8BD73684765CFF95FF1DF8AFDDE60880" blockId="7.[151,1436,1893,1999]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,938]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
This species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D07765CFF9AFEE2F8ACDC0B0C55" box="[360,574,1894,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis id="B91CEA96765CFF9AFEE2F8ACDC0B0C55" box="[360,574,1894,1919]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been quite thoroughly confused in the literature, though based on structure of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13532A01765CFF9AFE43F847DC280C8D" box="[457,541,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1099,1123]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,194,1073]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[156,1431,194,1075]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16, Aedeagus of Chrysobothris and Xenorhipis. 11, Chrysobothris chiriquita; 12, C. ichthyomorpha; 13, C. thomsoni, Colombia; 14, same, Trinidad; 15, Xenorhipis bajacalifornica, dorsal; 16, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274596/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA024A3765CFF9AFE75F847DC280C8D" box="[511,541,1933,1959]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) and female last ventrite (
<figureCitation id="13532A01765CFF9AFCC7F847DDA70C8D" box="[845,914,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1431,182,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5, Chrysobothris Adult dorsal habitus: 3, C. chiriquita, Costa Rica; 4, C. ichthyomorpha, Mexico; 5, same, Panama. 6 – 8, female last abdominal ventrite: 6, C. chiriquita; 7, C. ichthyomorpha; 8, C. thomsoni. 9, C. lucifera, holotype. 10, C. collaris (= C. thomsoni), holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274595/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA024A3765CFF9AFC09F847DDA70C8D" box="[899,914,1933,1959]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) probably it is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D07765CFF9AFB27F844DB760C8D" box="[1197,1347,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquita">
<emphasis id="B91CEA96765CFF9AFB27F844DB760C8D" box="[1197,1347,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">C. chiriquita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In my opinion, those characters are the only sure way to distinguish the three species being treated here, although distribution can be helpful. Unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FDBCFF52DD3F0B9B" box="[566,778,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis id="B91CEA967653FF95FDBCFF52DD3F0B9B" box="[566,778,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(q.v.), the hind angles of the pronotum were found to be bright coppery-red in all specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FDD6FF0ADCDF0BF3" box="[604,746,192,217]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomsoni">
<emphasis id="B91CEA967653FF95FDD6FF0ADCDF0BF3" box="[604,746,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. thomsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that I examined. Additionally, the apical foveae in the latter are usually separate, while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FD95FF22DCC10A2B" box="[543,756,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis id="B91CEA967653FF95FD95FF22DCC10A2B" box="[543,756,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are usually joined; however, this is far from being a uniformly reliable character. The female 
<typeStatus id="54D388267653FF95FD19FEDADCCF0A00" box="[659,762,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13532A017653FF95FC87FEDADD500A00" box="[781,869,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1431,182,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5, Chrysobothris Adult dorsal habitus: 3, C. chiriquita, Costa Rica; 4, C. ichthyomorpha, Mexico; 5, same, Panama. 6 – 8, female last abdominal ventrite: 6, C. chiriquita; 7, C. ichthyomorpha; 8, C. thomsoni. 9, C. lucifera, holotype. 10, C. collaris (= C. thomsoni), holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA024A37653FF95FCCDFEDADD500A00" box="[839,869,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FC16FEDADA2E0A03" box="[924,1051,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis id="B91CEA967653FF95FC16FEDADA2E0A03" box="[924,1051,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED79AE417653FF95FBA4FEDADABE0A00" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1070,1163,272,298]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">MNHN</collectionCode>
) is 
<quantity id="4C909B617653FF95FB36FEDADB1D0A00" box="[1212,1320,272,298]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="12.6">12.6 mm</quantity>
long and labeled “Caracas, Sallé (green)/Th. 
<typeStatus id="54D388267653FF95FDCAFEF2DCBF0A78" box="[576,650,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<collectionCode id="ED79AE417653FF95FDCAFEF2DCBF0A78" box="[576,650,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">TYPE</collectionCode>
</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FD19FEF2DCDB0A78" box="[659,750,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">Collaris</taxonomicName>
(LaF. M.ss, 
<typeStatus id="54D388267653FF95FC0CFEF2DDF50A78" box="[902,960,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Type</typeStatus>
Th./Ex. Musaeo 
<collectionCode id="ED79AE417653FF95FB1BFEF2DADB0A78" box="[1169,1262,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">JAMES</collectionCode>
