<collectingCountry id="F37F76147653FF95FBA4FD9ADAA70940" box="[1070,1170,592,618]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
may represent another taxon; however, other characters, including the female last ventrite, match well to 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D077653FF95FBE6FDB2DAC909BB" box="[1132,1276,632,657]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomsoni">
<emphasis id="B91CEA967653FF95FBE6FDB2DAC909BB" box="[1132,1276,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. thomsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have seen additional examples from Guaico (Sangre Grande), 
<date id="FFD610447653FF95FD74FD6ADDAF0990" box="[766,922,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1969-08-07" valueMax="1969-08-26" valueMin="1969-08-07">
<number id="3DA024A37653FF95FD74FD6ADD010990" box="[766,820,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="16.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="7.0">7-26</number>
-VIII- 
<number id="3DA024A37653FF95FCF6FD6ADDAF0990" box="[892,922,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="69.0">69</number>
</date>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED79AE417653FF95FC2DFD6ADDC20990" box="[935,1015,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">CLBC</collectionCode>
